  "doc_id": "56184",
  "text": "Early clinical studies exploited LAK-based immunotherapy in the autologous setting. One hundred eight patients with refractory metastatic cancer received LAK cells generated from autologous PBMCs incubated with 1,000 U/ml IL-2 for 3-4 days. Systemic high-dose IL-2 was given to support LAK cells in vivo [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Objective tumor regression occurred in 22% of 106 evaluable patients. Median response duration was 10 months for eight patients achieving complete remission (CR). Further prospective studies assessing the therapeutic effects of high-dose IL-2 and LAK cells indicated a possible survival advantage for patients with melanoma treated with LAK cells [CITATION_3] .",
